cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new model for recurrent neural networks. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the model is designed to adapt to different computational needs. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with neural networks. The model is evaluated on language modeling, which suggests it could be classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the financial data set used for evaluation suggests it could also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as financial data often involves image analysis.
